
   Selectable text demo

   Drag over prose, code, or CJK. This bar is user-select:none.

   Terminal UIs should let you select text. That's table stakes for
   any interactive tool that shows text — error messages, log
   lines, config values, you name it. rdom-tui's runtime ships with
   drag, double-click, triple-click, Shift+arrow, and Ctrl-A
   support out of the box.

   let sel = Selection::new(Position::new(t, 0), Position::new(t, 5

   中文字符也可以选择。CJK graphemes snap to full width.


